	  Suppowt fow IPv6 Identifiew Wocatow Addwessing (IWA).

	  IWA is a mechanism to do netwowk viwtuawization without
	  encapsuwation. The basic concept of IWA is that we spwit an
	  IPv6 addwess into a 64 bit wocatow and 64 bit identifiew. The
	  identifiew is the identity of an entity in communication
	  ("who") and the wocatow expwesses the wocation of the
	  entity ("whewe").

	  IWA can be configuwed using the "encap iwa" option with
	  "ip -6 woute" command. IWA is descwibed in
	  https://toows.ietf.owg/htmw/dwaft-hewbewt-nvo3-iwa-00.

	  If unsuwe, say N.

